  "content": "The new mantra for structural biology is clear: make it open, make it fast, make it scalable.\n\nThe field has reached an inflection point. Progress is no longer defined by the accuracy of a single prediction, but by the power of inference at scale.\n\nBy running OpenFold3 on AMD Instinct MI300X and MI355X GPUs, we are seeing what becomes possible when long-standing computational and memory constraints are removed—unlocking faster, more scalable discovery.\n\nA huge thank you to Gagandeep Singh, Kristof Denolf, and the rest of the team for this work and for sharing these insights. \n\nThis is how we move from isolated demonstrations to production-grade throughput, accelerating the path to new therapeutics and precision medicine.\n \n@[AMD](urn:li:organization:1497) #AMD #OpenFold3 #AMDInstinct #togetherweadvance_medicalresearch #AMDBrandAmbassador",
